name: bs3206
description: 1. [Install docker](https://docs.docker.com/engine/install/). If installing the CLI version, ensure docker compose is also installed. In the terminal, run `docker compose version` to ensure all is ok before proceeding. 1. Install the `make` package via the package manager for your OS. If using mac, this will be [Homebrew](https://brew.sh) or [Chocolatey](https://chocolatey.org) for windows, if these are not already installed then you will need to do this first. In a terminal, run `make --version` to ensure it's installed successfully.
